{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, possible reflections from the top boundary may also affect the flow, so that at some point the density may become negative and the simulation crashes.",
    "The action of the PML layer in a 2D configuration is demonstrated by an example of a monochromatic acoustic wave propagation through a solar-like stratified atmosphere.",
    "The equilibrium profiles are the same as in the previous Alfvén test, but without a magnetic field.",
    "The wave is triggered in the middle of the bottom boundary with 20 s period and 10 m s -1 initial amplitude, the top boundary condition has 25 grid points PML and the sides have 15 grid points PML.",
    "Figure 8 shows the 2D distribution of the vertical velocity at time moment t = 450 s, when the wave propagates in a quasisteady way."
  ]
}